<section id="prior-filer">
<h2><span class="label">Section 04</span>Prior-Filer Rate (Chapter 13)</h2>
<p>Of Chapter 13 cases in W.D.N.Y. with a coded prior-filing flag in the FJC IDB, <strong>20.53%</strong> (22,171 cases) carry a recorded prior bankruptcy filing. This metric is relevant to 11 U.S.C. §&nbsp;1328(f) discharge eligibility.</p>
<p>National rank on Chapter 13 prior-filer rate: <strong>72nd of 94</strong> (24th percentile).</p>
<p class="datastamp">Classified subset: 107,983 of 124,443 Chapter 13 cases. <a href="/research/methodology/#prior-filer-rate-chapter-13">How this is computed.</a></p>
</section>
<section id="pro-se">
<h2><span class="label">Section 05</span>Pro Se Filing Rate</h2>
<p>Of classified W.D.N.Y. filings, <strong>1.74%</strong> (3,966 cases) were filed without an attorney of record.</p>
<p>National rank on pro se rate: <strong>71st of 94</strong> (26th percentile).</p>
<p class="datastamp">Classified subset: 228,164 of 246,551 cases. <a href="/research/methodology/#pro-se-rate">How this is computed.</a></p>
</section>
